# Code of Conduct

## Introduction

We are dedicated to providing a respectful and inclusive environment for everyone who contributes to or interacts with our project. This Code of Conduct outlines our expectations for behavior and aims to foster a positive and collaborative community.

## Expected Behavior

- Be respectful and considerate towards others, regardless of their background, identity, or experience.
- Use welcoming and inclusive language.
- Be open to different viewpoints and experiences.
- Show empathy and kindness towards others.
- Exercise patience and understanding in discussions and disagreements.
- Be mindful of the impact of your words and actions on others.

## Unacceptable Behavior

The following behaviors are considered unacceptable within our community:

- Harassment, discrimination, or any form of offensive behavior towards others.
- Trolling, insulting, or derogatory comments, both in public and private interactions.
- Any form of unwelcome advances, including but not limited to sexual advances and inappropriate comments.
- Intimidation or bullying, either online or in-person.
- Publishing or displaying others' private information without their consent.
- Any behavior that causes another person to feel unsafe or unwelcome in the community.

## Reporting and Enforcement

If you witness or experience any behavior that violates this Code of Conduct, we encourage you to report it promptly to the project maintainers. You can contact us by [email/contact method]. All reports will be treated with strict confidentiality.

In order to maintain a safe and inclusive environment, we reserve the right to take appropriate action in response to any reported behavior. This may include warning the offender, issuing temporary or permanent bans, or taking other measures we deem necessary to address the situation.

